                      "name": "Shades",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Ronova is one of the four Shades.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 7073,
                      "icon_url": "",
                      "menu_id": 10,
                      "name": "Владыка Ночи",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Under Ronova's guidance, the Lord of the Night created the Night Kingdom in Natlan.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 7074,
                      "icon_url": "",
                      "name": "Шбаланке",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Ronova gave powers to the first Pyro Archon. With it, the rules of Natlan were established: the Ode of Resurrection and the Pilgrimage of the Return of the Sacred Flame.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 7299,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-webstatic.hoyoverse.com/event-static-hoyowiki-admin/2024/12/30/2f098b1f15854fd9dafc54998795a59e_864981592196815761.png",
                      "menu_id": 2,
                      "name": "Mavuika",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "The last Pyro Archon used the power of the divine throne and Ronova's power to fight with the Abyss. The price for the Ruler of Death's power is death.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 7417,
                      "icon_url": "",
                      "name": "Capitano",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "The Ruler of Death cast a curse of immortality on the Khaenri'ahns, including the Sentient Knight. The Captain sacrificed himself instead of Mavuika for using Ronova's powers. He wanted to use the shade's rules against her. To sustain the curse of immortality, the Ruler of Death relinquishes her demand for the price of \"death.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          }
